items.title: Sarah Mullally Is Named as First Female Archbishop of Canterbury
items.description: Sarah Mullally, the bishop of London, will lead the Church of England. She has been a vocal supporter of the rights of women in the church.

items.title: Manchester Synagogue Attack Fuels Fears of Antisemitism in Britain
items.description: In the hours after an attack, a blanket of fear and grief fell over synagogues and Jewish community centers across the country.

items.title: ‘Czech Trump’ Andrej Babis Is Poised to Return as Prime Minister in Elections
items.description: The party of Andrej Babis, former leader of the Czech government, is expected to prevail in parliamentary elections that begin Friday.
